                            <comment id="13935789" author="ndimiduk" created="Fri, 14 Mar 2014 23:01:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds like we should either fix or rip out those HTable constructors... &amp;#42;cough cough&amp;#42; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9117&quot; title=&quot;Remove HTablePool and all HConnection pooling related APIs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-9117&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-9117&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13935809" author="stack" created="Fri, 14 Mar 2014 23:17:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes.  Is &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9117&quot; title=&quot;Remove HTablePool and all HConnection pooling related APIs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-9117&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-9117&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; stalled?  Can we do some of it at least &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ndimiduk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ndimiduk&quot;&gt;Nick Dimiduk&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14126517" author="enis" created="Tue, 9 Sep 2014 03:16:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11797&quot; title=&quot;Create Table interface to replace HTableInterface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-11797&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-11797&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is done. This should depend on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11825&quot; title=&quot;Create Connection and ConnectionManager&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-11825&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-11825&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14140092" author="stack" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2014 06:44:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Purges stale javadoc and points folks instead to new way as described over in ConnectionFactory.  Is loud about not creating HTable instances directly.  Removes all that &apos;helpful&apos; stuff about connections being shared.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this patch is enough to get this blocker closed.  Nicks comment no long applies after the extensive Connection and Table refactor.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
