                            <comment id="14141015" author="stack" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2014 18:15:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can I have a +1 on this critical 0.99 issue?  Its a small review of a bit of javadoc.  The javadoc warnings are being handled elsewhere. The test failures are unrelated.  Tests dependent on being able to refer outside of the test directory to content in target, etc.  Seems like this no longer safe when concurrent checkouts running?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14141218" author="enis" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2014 20:16:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM. Thanks Stack. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you think we should also deprecate HTable and HBaseAdmin (in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10602&quot; title=&quot;Cleanup HTable public interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-10602&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-10602&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). There was some discussions around that elsewhere. For 1.0 interface users, HTable should not be used at all, but deprecating HTable will result in A LOT of deprecated code everywhere suddenly.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14141264" author="stack" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2014 20:43:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for +1 &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt; Applied to master and branch-1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On deprecating HTable and HBaseAdmin, if the constructors are shutdown, in essence they are effectively unavailable.  Deprecating them might be too radical a step.  On other hand, the landscape here is shifting fast and a nice clean API is starting to pop out..... How about asking the question again around 0.99.3?  The answer may be more plain then?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
